It begins in Damascus and passes through the Lebanese presidential palace in Baabda, the Lebanese government and the Lebanese intelligence apparatus," former Economy Minister Marwan Hamadeh, who was seriously hurt in an October car bombing that killed his driver, was quoted on LBC television as saying.
Hariri was buried in the unfinished mosque which he had financed after the mass funeral procession escorting an ambulance carrying  Hariri's coffin covered with national flag marched through the main streets to the mosque in central Beirut.
In the press conference, Saud dismissed a responsibility claim by a previously unknown group for Hariri's assassination as "ridiculous."
